**PAYG (Pay As You Go) withholding** is how employers deduct income tax from your pay each period on behalf of the ATO. The amount withheld depends on your gross pay, pay frequency, whether you have claimed the tax-free threshold ($18,200), and whether you have a HECS-HELP debt.

This calculator uses the **ATO's Schedule 1 withholding tax tables** for FY2025–26. It shows PAYG tax withheld per pay period, additional HECS-HELP withholding if applicable, total withheld, and estimated net pay.
